BlockingTaskRunnerHelper is self-contained so its thread can be

terminated when shutdown finishes without dependency issues.

entry.title: [keepalive-migration] Check mixed content when RFH is alive
entry.content:
- The existing implementation in Blink [1] does not block mixed

content [2] fetch keepalive requests, tracked by

https://crbug.com/1500989.

- The migration proxied fetch keepalive request loading via browser.

- After recent change [3], the proxied requests are handled in browser

first, and the redirects/responses will be forwarded back to

renderer later (if still alive). It is better for browser to perform

the same checks as what are done in renderer, including mixed content

checking.



[1]: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/blink/renderer/core/loader/frame_fetch_context.cc;l=660-663;drc=719c18366c0226fa751f38693b00f822d1b7ea9b

[2]: https://www.w3.org/TR/mixed-content/

[3]: https://crrev.com/c/4717687

entry.title: Avoid dangling pointer in TableHeader.
entry.content:
TableHeaders are often constructed inside ScrollViews. In that case,

- The ScrollView's contents is a TableView

- The ScrollView's header is a TableHeader with a raw pointer to the

TableView.



However, during destruction of the ScrollView its contents may be

destroyed before the header. When that happens, the TableHeader's

raw pointer to the TableView becomes dangling.



This CL therefore replaces the raw pointer from the TableHeader to the

TableView by a base::WeakPtr.



Bug: 1469136

entry.title: Reland: [PA] Add BUILDFLAG() guard to allocator_shim header and source code"
entry.content:
This CL is a reland of crrev.com/c/5009212. The reason why the CL was

reverted is that

allocator_shim_default_dispatch_to_linker_wrapped_symbols.cc was not

guarded by BUILDFLAG(USE_ALLOCATOR_SHIM). To avoid such a mistake,

add shim_headers and shim_sources to source_set("allocator_shim") and

apply the following way to initialize its sources:



shim_headers = [ "*.h" ]

shim_sources = [ "*.cc", "*.mm" ]

sources = shim_headers

if (use_allocator_shim) sources += shim_sources



This crrev.com/c/5020203 also fixes Android's all_dependent_configs,

i.e. wrap_malloc_symbols, and Apple's configs, i.e.

mac_no_default_new_delete_symbols and enable_arc. The configs needs

"if (use_allocator_shim)".

entry.title: [js-code-coverage] Enable coverage for shared and service workers
entry.content:
DevToolsAgentHost's extend base::RefCounted, when they are spawned for

non-worker types the places they are spawned grab a reference which

ensures the host is kept alive for the duration of the test.



However when a worker type is spawned the callee doesn't get a reference

to the host, this means after attaching the client to the host all

references are lost and the host gets destroyed. This leaves a race

condition where the host gets created, attached and destroyed THEN the

DevtoolsListener tries to start code coverage, however, the host has

been destroyed.



To avoid this race, let's grab a scoped_refptr to the DevToolsAgentHost

to ensure it doesn't get destroyed immediately. Along with this, let's

extend the DevToolsAgentCoverageObserver to log out the destroyed

lifecycle event.



There are a number of tests which have been disabled due to this

functionality, this test also enables all these tests.

entry.title: Promise app scale animation in shelf
entry.content:
Refactors the animation to replace a promise app with the installed app

item in shelf. Instead of copying the promise app view layer tree and

cross-fading the actual app view into the shelf, the promise item is

hidden immediately while the installed app item UI is initialized to

simulate promise app state - i.e. the icon is scaled down and the

progress indicator is shown. The app button view is then animated into

the final (default) app state. This makes animating more flexible, as it

enables animating the progress ring and the app icon view independently.



To prevent jankiness caused by delayed app icon load, the installed app

icon view is initialized to use the icon from the promise app. The icon

is then replaced after the scale in animation completes, and the actual

icon loads. Without this, there would be a flash of an empty icon just

after the promise app is hidden, and the installed app icon is shown.

entry.title: Use No-Vary-Search response header already in PrefetchContainer
entry.content:
Right now we are parsing the header into a new temporary

HttpNoVarySearchData object instead of using the HttpNoVarySearchData

object already stored in PrefetchContainer.



By using PrefetchContainer::GetNoVarySearchData() we also fix the

problem that the code parsing the header into a new temporary

HttpNoVarySearchData object is not guarded by

entry.title: [GenTSconfig] Update gen_tsconfig to allow custom definitions
entry.content:
Files app requires additional type definition files to exist in

tsconfig's "files" section, e.g. file_manager_private.js, the

current filter ".d.ts" doesn't support files which ends with .js.

This CL adds an additional command line args "custom_def_files"

to allow users to pass custom type definitions files via comma

separated values, e.g.



gen_tsconfig.py --root_out_dir out/Default --gen_target

"ui/file_manager:buld_ts" --custom_def_files

"file_manager_private.js,other_files.js"



The newly added arg is optional, so it won't break existing

functionalities.



Bug: b:289003444
